   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The flooding displaced over 5,152 families at total of 27,760 individuals (fews net report 18th May) . This came at time the Government and other actors were planning to resettle about 8,712 affected from the 2020 floods.These floods occur in an already difficult context, marked by the socio-economic effects of COVID-19 and the increase in cases of community transmission. Travel between neighborhoods following the floods could accelerate the chain of propagation. When moving, families risk living in sites with very narrow spaces where preventive measures against COVID-19</narrative>
  </description>
